{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legislate that employers must allow non-essential employees to work from home",
        "additional_details": "Accordingly, writing WFH into law for non-essential workplaces \u2013 as Scotland has done \u2013 would have a significant impact on the spread of COVID-19; decrease the risk to public health at this precarious time; offer legal recourse to employees facing disciplinary action for WFH; and be more in the spirit of a national lockdown.",
        "background": "Since March 2020, the government has advised people to work from home (WFH) in response to COVID-19. However, without being written into official legislation, many non-essential workplaces remain open and flout this advice by refusing to allow screen-based employees to WFH.",
